* Diana sniffed a bit as she lowered her snout from the wind, her cry 
seeming to unheard.
She wanted her mommy, her guard...anyone!
With a whimper and looked around, sniffing again in the shade of her pod, 
her tail not even swinging in the dry air of the desert.

Suddenly Diana spotted a small spotted spide running across the sand, the 
fur on her back rising and getting to her feet, hissing at it as it moved 
towards the shade of the pod.
She HATED spiders!
But it wasn't coming to get her mike she thought. The sands were very hot 
and the small bug needed to get all 8 of it's tiny feet off of it and into 
the shade.
But before the small spider could get to the shade Diana jumped at it, just 
to try and scar it off, spitting and hissing. Throwing a little sand towards 
the spider but only managing to slow it down.
The little arachnid then resuming it's journey towards the pod.
Diana jumped at it again but she jumped away as the spider raised it's two 
legs and bared its small fangs, too eager to get to the shade to let the 
faline keep it from it.

So Diana backed up into the scorching sunlight while the spider moved into 
the shade of her pod and then scurried under it, looking at where it 
disappeared for a moment before looking around herself with a small mew.
Already feeling the heat against her fur.
But then she hard something, snapping her head around and turning her ears 
this way and that.
Someone was yelling!
Someone! She wasn't alone out there!
Diana located the direction of the yelling, or what tshe thought it was, and 
began ti run towards it, her little white wings flapping in her hurry but 
not big enough to lift her off the ground.

She had to find out who was making all the noise. Maybe they could help 
her.*
